Prepare the Upload File for the Machine Learning Model

After building the machine learning model in your development environment, prepare an upload .zip file that meets all the requirements.

NOTE On August 1, 2024, you can no longer use externally built machine learning models in Einstein Discovery, and your prediction definitions that use an external model will fail. Instead, use Einstein Discovery to create a model.

File and folder names must match identically.

Required Components
NAME	COMPONENT	DESCRIPTION
data_processor.py	Python script	
validation.csv	Test Data	
saved_model.pb	TensorFlow model object	
assets/	folder	
variables/	folder	
saved_model.pkl	Scikit-learn model object	

This script must use the package versions described previously. It canâ€™t contain a non-standard library packages.

The data file must be in tabular format, contain one header row, and conform to RF4180 formatting.

TensorFlow Additional Required Components
NAME	COMPONENT	DESCRIPTION
saved_model.pb	TensorFlow model object	
assets/	folder	
variables/	folder

NAME	COMPONENT	DESCRIPTION
